no-iterator.description:
Description

This rule is aimed at preventing errors that may arise from using the__iterator__property, which is not implemented in several browsers. As such, it will warn whenever it encounters the__iterator__property.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-iterator: "error"*/

Foo.prototype.__iterator__ = function() {
    return new FooIterator(this);
};

foo.__iterator__ = function () {};

foo["__iterator__"] = function () {};

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-iterator: "error"*/

const __iterator__ = foo; // Not using the `__iterator__` property.
